Brief Introduction About Myself

Salma Belhamriti is a Moroccan biologist passionate about merging science, technology, and healthcare to create accessible solutions. Growing up with health challenges sparked her curiosity about the "why" behind medical issues, leading her from biology labs to health-tech innovation.
Currently building her expertise in healthcare technology and data with aspirations to become a Digital Healthcare Product Manager. Her mission: transform complex medical data into understandable stories, then turn those stories into affordable, meaningful solutions that help people enhance their health.

Her experience spans 840+ hours in pharmaceutical quality improvement at Hikma Pharmaceuticals, leading multidisciplinary projects like Easy Energy, and managing a gut-mind health app concept at ALX with complete wireframes, PRDs, and pitch presentations.
What makes her unique? Relentless curiosity, grit, and the drive for continuous learningâ€”she never gets bored of learning and seeking new fields to immerse herself in, constantly expanding her expertise to create meaningful impact in healthcare technology. 
